{"type":"turn_end","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my review of the arbitration record and admitted evidence, I have analyzed the case thoroughly. The key issue is whether Clavicular made a credible announcement that he and a partner were expecting a baby through pregnancy during the specified window.\n\nThe record shows:\n1. The Polymarket market resolved Yes after multiple dispute rounds\n2. Forbes reported the dispute centered on \"a streamer who told his audience he had gotten a girl pregnant\"\n3. The Domahhhh thread confirms Clavicular \"claimed/joked that he got a girl pregnant\" \n4. The KickChamp post shows a viral claim about a girlfriend pregnancy with 15.5M+ views\n5. However, the record lacks the original VOD, transcript, or direct statement from Clavicular\n6. Multiple sources describe the statement as ambiguous, vague, and potentially a joke\n7. The biological timeline (10 days) is flagged as medically implausible\n\nThe critical missing piece is the primary source - the actual words spoken by Clavicular in their original context. While there's evidence that some pregnancy-related statement circulated, the record consistently undermines its credibility through descriptions like \"claimed/joked,\" \"vague,\" \"no proof,\" and biological implausibility.\n\nUnder the preponderance standard, the plaintiff has not met the burden of showing that a credible announcement occurred. The evidence points more strongly toward viral rumor and ambiguous streamer content than a qualifying credible announcement under the market rule."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0d2c","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record lacks proof of a credible announcement. No primary source (VOD, transcript, or representative statement) is preserved; the Domahhhh thread describes the statement as 'claimed/joked' and 'vague'; and multiple sources flag the claim as implausible. While the market resolved Yes, the platform outcome cannot substitute for the missing credible announcement the rule requires.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":783,"output":415,"cacheRead":62784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782803793201,"responseId":"gen-1782803793-yhz18FXkX6pE1I875xNv"},"toolResults":[{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0d2c","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630065125\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 753871\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630065125\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:29:26.138665278Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":753871,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630065125\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 753871\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630065125\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:29:26.138665278Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":753871,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex09-20260630065125","member_id":"C4","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accept