ol":"read_evidence_range"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782803755286},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me decode this Gamma API evidence:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f8d5","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"\" | base64 -d"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":2478,"output":2204,"cacheRead":58112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62794,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782803755287,"responseId":"gen-1782803755-hsz5u5aYGI1v0GEOhdqI"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f8d5","toolName":"bash","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Source: https://gamma-api.polymarket.com/events?slug=clavicular-pregnancy-in-2026\nRetrieval: 2026-06-30T07:00Z by curl. Local full JSON saved privately at /aar-codex/artifacts/polymarket-gamma-clavicular-pregnancy-20260630.json; size 7273 bytes; sha256 38264d301c3adad29fef3b6e7116dfcaa7e2302903bde1c46457831ec1a41335.\n\nRelevant extracted fields from the returned JSON:\n- Event id: 400878\n- Ticker/slug: clavicular-pregnancy-in-2026\n- Title: Clavicular pregnancy in 2026?\n- Description/rule: This market resolves Yes if Clavicular announces that he and a partner are expecting a baby through pregnancy between market creation and December 31, 2026, 11:59 PM ET; otherwise No. Only credible announcements qualify; non-credible announcements, for example jokes, do not suffice. Resolution source is statements from Clavicular or representatives, though definitive consensus of credible media reporting may be considered.\n- Event creationDate/startDate: 2026-04-20T22:47:28.569518Z / 2026-04-20T22:47:28.569523Z.\n- Event endDate: 2026-12-31T00:00:00Z.\n- UpdatedAt in fetched JSON: 2026-06-30T02:49:27.136133Z.\n- Event active true, closed true, archived false, restricted true.\n- Event volume: 13934862.960998023; openInterest: 5749723.168803; commentCount: 1124.\n\nMarket object:\n- Market id: 2037907.\n- conditionId: 0x6747bae2269c348786d0c0c0f4286ac006f13f16325d4dcbab954b46de029f19.\n- questionID: 0x24b6bade3cce1deaee8a6381420b7fb88b0f409b447747471b0245061d986280.\n- outcomes: [\"Yes\", \"No\"].\n- outcomePrices: [\"1\", \"0\"].\n- closedTime: 2026-05-01 00:33:40+00; umaEndDate 2026-05-01T00:33:40Z.\n- umaResolutionStatus: resolved.\n- umaResolutionStatuses: [\"proposed\", \"disputed\", \"proposed\", \"disputed\"].\n- automaticallyResolved: true.\n- resolvedBy: 0x65070BE91477460D8A7AeEb94ef92fe056C2f2A7C.\n- lastTradePrice: 0.999; bestBid/bestAsk: 0.998 / 0.999.\n\nEvent metadata context_description in current API says trader consensus locked in a 99.9% implied probability for Yes, driven by Clavicular's repeated public vows to become a father by year-end, a fertility-stack reveal, and a controversial pitch for a dating show to select a baby mama from 500 contestants. It also describes debunked rumors of an 18-year-old girlfriend's pregnancy after just 10 days and says those rumors amplified the narrative of imminent fatherhood. This API metadata supports the existence of market momentum and final Yes, but it also shows the platform context was not limited to a clean verified pregnancy announcement."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782803793200},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my review of the arbitration record and admitted evidence, I have analyzed the case thoroughly. The key issue is whether Clavicular made a credible announcement that he and a partner were expecting a baby through pregnancy during the specified window.\n\nThe record shows:\n1. The Polymarket market resolved Yes after multiple dispute rounds\n2. Forbes reported the dispute centered on \"a streamer who told his audience he had gotten a girl pregnant\"\n3. The Domahhhh thread confirms Clavicular \"claimed/joked that he got a girl pregnant\" \n4. The KickChamp post shows a viral claim about a girlfriend pregnancy with 15.5M+ views\n5. However, the record lacks the original VOD, transcript, or direct statement from Clavicular\n6. Multiple sources describe the statement as ambiguous, vague, and potentially a joke\n7. The biological timeline (10 days) is flagged as medically implausible\n\nThe critical missing piece is the primary source - the actual words spoken by Clavicular in their original context. While there's evidence that some pregnancy-related statement circulated, the record consistently undermines its credibility through descriptions like \"claimed/joked,\" \"vague,\" \"no proof,\" and biological implausibility.\n\nUnder the preponderance standard, the plaintiff has not met the burden of showing that a credible announcement occurred. The evidence points more strongly toward viral rumor and ambiguous streamer content than a qualifying credible announcement under the market rule."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0d2c","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record lacks proof of a credible announcement. No primary source (VOD, transcript, or representative statement) is preserved; the Domahhhh thread describes the statement as 'claimed/joked' and 'vague'; and multiple sources flag the claim as implausible. While the market resolved Yes, the platform outcome cannot substitute for the missing credible announcement the rule requires.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":783,"output":415,"cacheRead":62784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782803793201,"responseId":"gen-1782803793-yhz18FXkX6pE1I875xNv"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0d2c","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630065125\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 753871\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630065125\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:29:26.138665278Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":753871,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630065125\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 753871\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630065125\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:29:26.138665278Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":753871,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex09-20260630065125","member_id":"C4","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-30T07:29:26.138665278Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C4","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C4","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":753871,"role_id":"council","turn_number":12}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782803812270},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My vote has been accepted. I have voted \"not_demonstrated\" because the admitted record does not establish by a preponderance of the evidence that Clavicular made a credible announcement of an existing partner pregnancy. The key deficiencies are:\n\n1. No preserved primary source (original VOD, transcript, or representative statement)\n2. The Domahhhh thread describes the statement as \"claimed/joked\" and \"vague\" \n3. Multiple sources flag the claim as biologically implausible\n4. While the market resolved Yes, the platform outcome cannot substitute for the missing credible announcement that the rule specifically requires\n\nThe evidence points more toward viral rumor and ambiguous streamer content than a qualifying credible announcement under the market's standards."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":352,"output":150,"cacheRead":63808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782803812271,"responseId":"gen-1782803812-xf56B1fTOVdCtkxksWTx"}],"willRetry":false}
